        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I kept finding the need to conditionally issue SoapServer faults outside of the scope of classes or functions being handled by SoapServer.\n\nTo issue a SoapServer fault, you merely need to call SoapServer::fault($code, $message, ...), but from what I can deduce, Zend_Soap_Server has no public method to retrieve the instance of SoapServer it is using.\n\nOne fix is to make Zend_Soap_Server::_getSoap() a public method.  Alternatively, I chose to add an $issueFault flag to Zend_Soap_Server::fault().  By default, it will not issue a SoapServer fault, but if set to true, a fault will be issued with the message and code provided.\n\nI have supplied the diff.\n\nPlease let me know if I'm off base in my attempt or am missing some simple way to externally issue a SoapServer fault through Zend_Soap_Server."
        },
